                <Gloss>to provide in abundance</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to provide a great deal of</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to cause to be abundant</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In some languages, however, it may be very strange to speak of having or receiving an abundance of grace. The closest equivalent for {S:04900100700004}-{S:04900100800000} may be ‘grace which he caused us to experience abundantly’ or ‘grace which he showed to us in an abundant way.’</Comments>
