        <LEXMeaning Id="003958001004000" IsBiblicalTerm="Y" EntryCode="78.31" Indent="0">
          <LEXDomains>
            <LEXDomain>Degree</LEXDomain>
          </LEXDomains>
          <LEXSubDomains>
            <LEXSubDomain>More Than, Less Than [Comparative Degree]</LEXSubDomain>
          </LEXSubDomains>
          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-12-24 14:13:46" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>a degree which is considerably in excess of some point on an implied or explicit scale of extent</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>very great</Gloss>
                <Gloss>excessive</Gloss>
                <Gloss>extremely</Gloss>
                <Gloss>emphatic</Gloss>
                <Gloss>surpassing</Gloss>
                <Gloss>all the more</Gloss>
                <Gloss>much greater</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In {S:05000100900024} it is clear that μᾶλλον καὶ μᾶλλον (see {D:78.28}) serves to emphasize the degree expressed in περισσεύω. The verb περισσεύητε in {S:05200400100056} may be regarded as a kind of substitute verb referring to περιπατεῖτε and indicating essentially a matter of degree. This is, of course, further reinforced by {L:μᾶλλον&lt;SDBG:μᾶλλον:000000&gt;} ({D:78.28}).</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
          </LEXSenses>
