        <LEXMeaning Id="003958001005000" IsBiblicalTerm="Y" EntryCode="78.32" Indent="0">
          <LEXDomains>
            <LEXDomain>Degree</LEXDomain>
          </LEXDomains>
          <LEXSubDomains>
            <LEXSubDomain>More Than, Less Than [Comparative Degree]</LEXSubDomain>
          </LEXSubDomains>
          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-12-24 14:13:46" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>to cause an increase in the degree of some experience or state{N:001}</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to cause to be intense</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to cause to be more</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to cause to grow</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>It would seem that πλεονάσαι and περισσεύσαι in {S:05200301200014} simply reinforce the meaning of intense degree. It is assumed that these two expressions are not completely synonymous, but it is difficult to determine precisely how they may contrast. It may simply be that περισσεύσαι is somewhat more emphatic.</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
          </LEXSenses>
