          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-12-24 14:13:46" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>to experience superior benefit or advantage, implying some type of comparison</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to have a greater benefit</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to experience a superior advantage</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In indicating ‘a superior advantage’ it may be necessary to be quite specific about the basis for the comparison. For example, in {S:04600800800032} it may be necessary to translate as ‘if we do eat, we will be no better off than if we did not eat,’ and in {S:04500300900006} one may translate ‘what then; are we decidedly better off than the others are?’</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
